Create a Google Ads Connection for Segment Intelligence

To set up a new Google Ads connection for Segment Intelligence, create an external credential, a connection, and a data stream to bring in data.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To set up Segment Intelligence:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
1. Set Up an External Credential for Google Ads
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Named Credentials, and then select Named Credentials.
On the External Credentials tab, click New.
Enter a label and a name for your external credential. The name can’t contain spaces. You can use underscores.
For Authentication Protocol, select OAuth 2.0.
For Authentication Flow Type, select Browser Flow.
For Authentication Provider, select Google Ads Data Cloud.
Save your changes.
In the external credential that you created, under Principals, click New.
Enter a name. You can include spaces.
For Identity Type, select Named Principal.
Set the Sequence Number to 1, and save your changes.
Authenticate your external credential principal.
Under Principals, from the Actions dropdown menu, select Authenticate.
From the Google Authenticator, select the account that you’re pulling data for.
To connect Data Cloud to Google Ads, click Allow.
After you authenticate, the status changes to Configured.
Define the Named Credential.
In Named Credentials, click New and enter a label and name. The name can’t contain spaces. You can use underscores.
Enter https://google.com in the URL.
For External Credentials, select the external credential that you created.
Save your changes.
Enable External Credentials Access.
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Profiles, and then select Profiles.
Click System Administrator.
On the Enable External Credential Principal Access tab, click Edit.
Select the external credential principal you created and add it to Enabled External Credentials Principals.
Save your changes.
2. Create a Connection Between Data Cloud and Google Ads
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Connectors, and then select Connectors.
Create a Google Ads connector.
Click New.
Select the Google Ads connector and click Next.
Enter the connection name and connection API name.
Select the named credential that you created.
Enter your Google customer ID.
Save your changes.

To complete the connection, create a new Google Ads data stream to view your data. See Create a Google Ads Data Stream for Segment Intelligence.
